name: The Story of a Startup #3
caption: The Story of a Startup #3
description:
In Story of a Startup #3, we would like to welcome first female entrepreneur @[100002795096430:2048:Sabrine Assem] the founder and managing director of Untap LLC. Untap is an innovation agency with a focus on “Open Innovation”, “Consumer Co-Creation”, and “Crowdsourcing”. 
Sabrine is a public relations consultant at the German-Arab Chamber of Commerce. She is also founded “SolverMine”; one of the first open innovation platforms in the Middle East.
Sabrine is a former teaching assistant of information systems at the German University in Cairo (GUC). She is a management consultant and a researcher at a number of entities such as Global Projects Partners e.V., General Authority for Investment, Nutty Scientists Egypt, and more. She is a graduate of the German University in Cairo with majors in Innovation and Information Systems.
Over the past year, she prepared and gave around 40 workshops and sessions on strategy, business model innovation, market research, growth hacking, and product development to over 100 Egyptian and Arab entrepreneurs within local and regional projects sponsored by the German Federal Ministry for Economic Affairs and Energy and the Canadian organization “Taking IT Global”.
